******
[1] Cholera - Cote d'Ivoire (Bas-Sassandra District)
Date: Thu 8 Jan 2015
Source: FratMat [in French, machine transl, edited]
http://fratmat.info/une/item/21729-choléra-8-nouveaux-cas-déclarés-à-tabléguikou-à-divo


Cholera, which seemed to be under control, continues to haunt the people of the village of Tableguikou in the sub-prefecture of Divo. In effect, according to the director of the regional hospital center, 8 new cases of cholera have been confirmed on Wed 7 Jan 2015. 5 among them are hospitalized the health center in the village and 3 in Divo. For the moment, there were no deaths, according to him. Divo has taken the decision to close all potentially unhealthy to shelter the population of Tableguikou.

It should be pointed out that the cholera outbreak was declared on 22 Dec 2014, and has left 5 dead among 19 infected persons. In 2002, cholera killed 14 persons in the village when hydraulic pumps failed.

[Byline: Soumaila Bakayoko]

