******
[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Rivers State)
Date: Mon 5 Jan 2015
Source: The Tide [edited]
http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2015/01/05/cholera-hits-andoni/


A cholera outbreak may have claimed the lives of some children in Andoni local Government Area. Some of the affected communities include Ngo Ukwa Agana, Okoloile, Ebukuma among others.

Residents blamed the incident on the absence of potable drinking water in the affected communities. Some residents told The Tide that the absence of good drinking water made the communities depend on water which has no official safety approval.

The Tide also learned that the absence of medical personnel at the General Hospital at Ngo has led some residents to patronize private and herbal medical practitioners, adding that some patients squeeze water from bitterleaf to treat vomiting and stooling.

When The Tide visited the local Government Secretariat at Ngo, all the offices were under lock and key as the workers were said to be on holiday, while at the Ngo General Hospital, some nurses were seen battling to save the lives of some children brought by their parents.

[Byline: John Bibor]

